MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: All right. I have to meet with the commander of the encampment to discuss a joint operation with the Eisengrad army.

I don't know much about it, but it seems like it.
Just as I said that, there was an exclamation from the soldiers who were distributing the luggage.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Oh, that's my outfit! The one I'm wearing now is a little dirty. I asked for a new one so that I can put all my energy into the mission.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: I'll make up for my mistake during the mission! I'll take down all those monsties! It's all their fault that the world isn't at peace and that I placed the wrong order! It's all because of the monsties!

The mission to investigate the latest situation regarding the phantom mist began two days later than planned. This was because it took two days to get the uniforms of the Eisengrad army soldiers who participated in the joint operation.
Surrounded by a mountain of brightly colored girls' clothes, none of the soldiers were angry at the teary-eyed, apologetic Oculus. In fact, they were laughing. Good grief.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Hm? Is something missing?

One of the soldiers took something out of a box labeled "Clothing"
and showed it to us.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Huh? Seriously? Everything in the box was girls' clothing? That can't be true. They're all the same outfit. Who ordered the wrong clothing? Wait—I'm the one who did the ordering!
With a big smile on her face, Oculus received the brand-new outfit from the soldier. However, her face gradually turned white. One by one, the soldiers handed her new clothes.
Oculus was always in the lead during the mission. Her power to move forward without fear of failure may one day clear the mist from this world.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
Sorry! I'm so sorry! I'm so so sorry! This is a nightmare!
I tried so hard, but I ruined it all right at the last minute!

We also need to make an application to the Alliance headquarters to conduct the operation.
Things are getting busy.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
Why don't you leave the order list to me?
I'll go around and ask the soldiers what they really need.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: But I asked them about it earlier while I was handing out the food. They said that the commander is a nice person but he's super stubborn. He confiscates any magazines the soldiers try to bring in.

Yeah, I guess so.
No, wait.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Of course, I'll stock up on magazines for the female soldiers, too. You don't have to say a word! It's fine! I'd never divulge anyone's sexuality!
Yeah! barked the soldiers.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
Thank you, Queenie. We're short on clothing, not just food. Don't fight!
I ordered enough so that everyone will get what they need! Also, those things are individually wrapped, so make sure you check the name tags!
Oculus smiles at the exasperated Queensway.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Queensway
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Err, just what is going on here?

As soon as Oculus shouted,
half-naked soldiers appeared from the surrounding tents, carting around the supplies in a frenzy.

When we returned, we handed over the supplies we had collected and told them what had happened.
In an instant, the soldiers in the camp became lively and animated.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
Hey, they said we could take the stuff!
Come on, guys!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
Wow, Queenie, I feel like I haven't seen you in ages!
I'll take the supplies you brought with you.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Queensway
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
I have arrived with six train knights. We have brought some supplies.
Oh, it looks like the situation isn't as bad as I'd heard.
Her dedicated work healed not only the minds of the soldiers but also their bodies, and the encampment began to rapidly get into better operational shape.

That's not what I'm talking about.
Ah, but Oculus has already run off.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: OK, I'll change the bandage so pull down your pants. Don't be shy, it'll make me uncomfortable too! What? My clothes are dirty too? Oh, yeah. I couldn't get the stains off even after washing them. Guess I'll take them off too!

While we were planning the operation, Oculus worked as hard as she could. She ran from one end of the encampment to the other, even giving orders to the local staff, but no one gave her a hard time about it.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Don't expect my food to taste good! You were so happy to eat it the day we brought back the supplies, so just shut up and eat! It's nutritious and that's what matters!

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Don't you have anything to wear? I only had a little detergent, so I washed everything at once. Will you wrap yourself in a blanket and sleep until your clothes dry? I'll bring your food to your tent.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Queensway
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Yeah, sure. But there's a lot, you know? I don't think you can carry it all by yourself. And as for calling me Queenie...

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Yes, yes, don't push me. There's enough for everyone. I told you not to push!
The food would be cooked before it went off. The clothing and other items were also distributed to those in need. The soldiers who had received the food and supplies expressed their thanks to Oculus.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
If you want to thank someone, you should thank the merchants who carried the supplies.
We didn't do anything special.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Yes, yes, move it. If you can move, please help me. Man, why is the supply storehouse so far away? We'll have to move the command center's big tent right over there, and we'll move the storehouse there.
Err, no, I'm sure there are other things they need more.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: That's sad, right? It must be very frustrating. That kind of thing is necessary, isn't it? Don't you agree?

It seems that the military's intel does not reflect the changing situation. We need to conduct new investigations on the appearance of the phantom mist. I'll have the backup train knights who are standing by form a unit. We can leave the transportation of supplies to them.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase:
Got it!
I've just gotta check the number of dirty magazines they might need.
Oculus smiled with satisfaction knowing that the merchants who had abandoned their cargo and fled were more happy to see us than anyone else.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Queensway
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Conductor, what does she mean by "those things"? There were a lot of individually wrapped magazines among the supplies.
When she says, "those things," she means "those things."

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Queensway
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: You mean there is a magazine called "Those Things"? I've never heard of it before, but if everyone is so excited to receive one, it must be a very good magazine.

MSceneDetailViewModel.Name: Oculus
MSceneDetailViewModel.Phrase: Now, we'd better order additional supplies. It's just that the route being used at the moment is too dangerous. I didn't realize the attack zone was that close.

Will the commander complain? Well, I'll deal with that when it happens.
A person in charge spends half of their time apologizing anyway.
